        "path": "/books/nahj-al-balagha:3:219:1",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/3/346/423",
        "text": [
          "٣٤٦. وَقَالَ (عليه ‏السلام): مَاءُ وَجْهِكَ جَامِدٌ يُقْطِرُهُ السُّؤَالُ، فَانْظُرْ عِنْدَ مَنْ تُقْطِرُهُ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
            "346. Amīr al-mu’minīn, peace be upon him, said: The dignity of your face is solid but begging dissolves it away; therefore, look carefully before whom you dissolve it."
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
